hackathon-description-text: Come be a part of Wayfair's
hackathon-eligibility: Non-Wayfair employees may participate, but must be invited and partnered with a Wayfair employee present at the event.
hackathon-rules:
Wayfair code of conduct rules and Hackathon code of conduct rules apply: 
By participating in this event, you agree to abide by the items outlined above. People violating these will be asked to leave at the discretion of event staff.

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: You will be asked to present the project in front of a small and large group. Presentation thoroughness and execution will be considered.
A winning criteria for a project is to show the most innovative idea. Something conceptually new or interesting.
Projects do not have to be Wayfair-specific, but we will consider each project in terms of how applicable it is to Wayfair's engineering needs.
We will look at projects as a whole and consider how useful they might be to engineers in any field.
